# Example for Caddy (https://caddyserver.com/) on the same host as Docker Compose.
# Prefer the shared multi-site config in the `proxy_service` Git repo (Docker + `xraes_proxy` + path `/fryeIslandGolf`).

# 1. Point DNS A/AAAA for www.xraes.com and xraes.com to this server.
# 2. `docker network create xraes_proxy` (or start the proxy stack first), set PUBLIC_PATH_PREFIX=/fryeIslandGolf, then `docker compose up` for this app.
# 3. The legacy all-in-one case: if you proxy only to localhost, expose the web service on 8080 and:
#    Install Caddy, copy the site blocks below to /etc/caddy/Caddyfile, then: sudo systemctl reload caddy

# www.xraes.com {
#	encode gzip zstd
#	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
# }
# xraes.com {
#	redir https://www.xraes.com{uri} permanent
# }
